# Context

## Background
The prior shadcn-inspired token pass still looked too similar because the page silhouette remained a full-width document: header, hero, sections, cards.

## Why This Way
This follow-up changes the visible shell rather than only component polish. Generated previews now render inside a bounded app canvas on a neutral page background, with a floating bordered nav, active nav state, contained footer, and more distinct route bands. The goal is for the default output to read as an intentional static prototype surface instead of a Pico document.

## Verification
Ran typecheck, tests, build, root strict eval, and strict eval on regenerated 10-route music, clinic, and museum live prototypes. Captured the music home preview with agent-browser to confirm the silhouette changed.
